## Detection

The investigation identified a phishing campaign using a fake Microsoft login page hosted on attacker-controlled infrastructure.

Key findings included:

* Suspicious emails sent to SwiftSpend Financial employees
* A sender address impersonating accounts payable activity
* A phishing domain hosting a fake Microsoft login page
* Directory listing enabled on the phishing web server
* An exposed phishing kit archive
* Captured credential logs left accessible on the server
* A phishing kit configured to exfiltrate credentials to an external email address
* VirusTotal detections classifying the archive as phishing and Trojan-related

